CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, National edition, April 4, 1942, pg. 13, reads: "Courier's 'Double V' Girl of the Week - Glamorous Fredi Washington, of stage and screen fame, has joined the campaign for victory at home and abroad. On a visit to Pittsburgh last week, the pretty star said, 'I am proud to enlist in Courier's crusade against our enemies abroad and those at home who would deny us full rights as Americans.  You have my wholehearted support.' - (Harris photo.)"
TitMainTitle: Fredi Washington posed on sidewalk overlooking Soldiers and Sailors Memorial Hall and Cathedral of Learning, University of Pittsburgh, Oakland
